records.addlTxt:
Defendant Christopher Roberson in court with attorney Michael Jude.  Sara Nicole Volden Schroeder appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Deputy Court Clerk ssm.  

Defendant changes his plea to GUILTY.  Defendant examined as to his plea, advised of his Constitutional rights and the maximum penalty.   Defendant advised that if not a United States Citizen, deportation is possible.  Court found that defendant knowingly, voluntarily and intelligently waived his rights.  Guilty Plea Questionnaire/Waiver of Rights and Addendum received and filed.  Parties stipulate to the complaint as a factual basis to sustain defendant's plea.  Court found defendant guilty and ordered a Judgment of Conviction be entered on the record.  

Sentencing proceeded.  Statements by the State, defense and defendant.  Defendant sentenced to serve 9 months in the House of Correction with credit for 2 days time served.  Court STAYED the sentence and placed defendant on Probation with the State of Wisconsin, Department of Corrections for a period of 1 year.
Conditions:
*  Participate in parenting classes;
*  Perform 30 hours of community service;
*  Defendant is to be enrolled in school to obtain GED/HSED by January, 2016; 
*  Possess no guns;
*  Submit a DNA sample and pay the DNA surcharge;
*  Pay all costs and surcharges or, if not paid, convert to a civil judgment.

If the defendant successfully completes probation and commits no new crimes, the Court will grant expungement.  Notice of Right to Seek Postconviction Relief received and filed.
